Here are ten sentences that each end with the word "apple":

1. For a healthy snack, I decided to eat a crisp red apple.
2. The teacher smiled when the student placed a shiny apple on her desk.
3. In the heart of the orchard, we found the perfect apple.
4. She baked a delicious pie using only the sweetest apple.
5. The logo on the computer is a simple silhouette of an apple.
6. He compared the two fruits and realized one was not an apple.
7. Snow White took a bite of the poisoned apple.
8. My favorite color is the bright green of a Granny Smith apple.
9. The archer aimed his arrow directly at the target apple.
10. Nothing tastes quite like a fresh, cold apple. [end of text]


